aboutPageBusinessAdvisorBlurb.en-US: Gabrielle has worked in college admission counseling since 2000 and at Castilleja School since 2014. Gabrielle served as Assistant Director of Admission at both the San Francisco Conservatory of Music and Stanford University before moving to college counseling posts as Associate Director of College Counseling at St. Margarets Episcopal School, San Juan Capistrano, and Sacred Heart Schools, Atherton.

aboutPageHeaderTitle.en-US: We make college applications simple, straight-forward, and pleasant.

aboutPageHeaderSubtitle.en-US: We believe that everybody should have an equal opportunity to participate in the future. Were taking on a big, audacious goal  not because its easy, but because its hard.

aboutPageWhoWeAreContent.en-US:
Cialfo started in 2016 with one mission: to increase transparency and accessibility of college information. 

Our team is made up of former college counselors, educators, and technology professionals working to change how the world approaches post-secondary education. And our platform emerges from the real world experiences of those we serve, whether theyre a devoted counselor or a steadfast principal.

aboutPagePartnersTitle.en-US: Building an ecosystem for college applications

aboutPagePartnersSubtitle.en-US: Cialfo partners with leading organizations shaping the future of education.

sendTitle.en-US: Send transcripts and letters of recommendations to colleges

sendFooterQuote.en-US: It's an invaluable tool to manage the application process, keep track of students, send messages, upload documents to unis, and support the students.

aboutPageHeaderTitle.en-US: Now coming to a city near you

aboutPageHeaderSubtitle.en-US: Find out where the team at Cialfo is hosting our next event, and what conferences well be attending.

eventsSubfooterQuote.en-US: Well be attending International ACAC 2019 in London, Ontario and hosting several events while were there. Join us and learn how Cialfo can help you and your school find success in college applications.

eventsCialfoSessionsBlurb.en-US: Cant make it to an event in-person? Tune into one of our live sessions or office hours and learn more about Cialfo - from the basics to the advanced tips and tricks.

eventsCialfoEventsBlurb.en-US: Connect with Cialfo and our community of schools, education partners, and power users at one of our regional events - or find us at an upcoming conference.

researchInfoTitle.en-US: All the information you need, in one place

researchTranscriptTitle.en-US: Keep track of and compare against admissions outcomes

researchKnowledgeTitle.en-US: Turn personal knowledge into common knowledge

researchFooterQuote.en-US: Cialfo is a great help to the counselor and the students too. It has everything served on a platter - easy to pick and easy to work with.

getInTouchMessagePlaceholder.en-US: Leave a message and a member of our team will be in touch as soon as possible.

getInTouchSubfooterBlurb.en-US: Cialfo work with our ideas and want to work with out feedback. That team feeling is great. That's a major reason we chose them.

aboutPageBusinessAdvisorBlurb.en-US: Peggy brings 25 years of college counseling experience to our board. In her previous roles, Peggy was Vice Principal of Academic Affairs and College Counseling at Saint Lawrence Academy, Director of College Counseling at Pinewood School, and Director of College Counseling at Notre Dame High School. Peggy earned her Ph.D in Psychology from Columbia University. She currently instructs at UC Berkeley Extension and UCLA Extension's College Counseling Certificate Program.

bulletPoint.en-US: Plot student scores on a scattergram across your school - or the Cialfo network at large

aboutPageBusinessAdvisorBlurb.en-US: After earning his undergraduate degree from Bowdoin College, Jeff began his career in education, first in admissions but then focusing on English. He earned his masters degree in English from Middlebury College and then moved to college counseling full-time, having found his passion. Jeff is currently working on his doctorate in Education.

homePageHeaderTitle.en-US: Create, manage and track college applications
homePageHeaderTitle.zh-CN: Create, manage and track college applications

homePageHeaderBlurb.en-US: From scheduling college visits to sending electronic documents and building matriculation reports, Cialfo is where college applications flow.

homePageSchoolTestimonialsTitle.en-US: The top private schools trust Cialfo

homePageFeaturesSendDocumentBlurb.en-US: Cialfo integrates with the Common Application and Parchment. Manage and send transcripts and letters of recommendation to colleges in one place.

homePageFeaturesLeverageBlurb.en-US: Your students are going global, and Cialfo reflects that. Our rich database of colleges all over the world provides financial aid data, course information, essay prompts and deadlines for major U.S schools, and historical acceptance rates.

homePageFeaturesDiscoverBlurb.en-US: How many students were accepted, rejected, or waitlisted? Whats your school profile? What are your students MBTI types or career interests? Cialfos robust reporting tools offers a 360 view of your students, drilling down into their learning styles or application histories.

homePageVideoCaseStudyTitle.en-US: Cialfo drives college applications at forward thinking schools.

bulletPoint.en-US: Add, manage, and email college reps right from Cialfo - no more lengthy email threads and half-forgotten phone numbers.

featuresTitle.en-US: All the features you need to get students to college

featurePageSchoolTestimonialsTitle.en-US: The top private schools trust Cialfo

featurePageFeaturesSendDocumentBlurb.en-US: Use our Parchment and Common Application integrations to send documents and transcripts securely to colleges. Request, manage, and send documents right from within Cialfo.

featurePageFeaturesLeverageBlurb.en-US: Explore Cialfo's database of colleges, complete with tuition costs, essay prompts, and even location information.

featurePageFeaturesDiscoverBlurb.en-US: How many students were accepted, rejected, or waitlisted? What are your most popular schools? Cialfo puts the power of data in your hands.

fourOhFourText.en-US: Sorry, we can't find the page you were looking for!

aboutPageBusinessAdvisorBlurb.en-US: Not only is Katy the Director of College Counseling at Bellarmine College Preparatory, but she also serves as an instructor at UC Berkeley and UCLA Extension's College Counseling Certificate Program. Katy was formerly President for NACAC and WACAC, and holds a B.A. in Political Science from Whittier College.

bulletPoint.en-US: Empower everyone in your team to make data-driven decisionswhether that's your counseling team, your school, or an entire district.
Explore 25000+ colleges in 36 countries with rankings, statistics, and financial data.
Quickly generate reports on everything you could possibly need, then download them in Excel or PDF for further analysis and sharing.
Add, manage, and email college reps right from Cialfo - no more lengthy email threads and half-forgotten phone numbers.
Discover school demographics: the teacher to student ratio, enrollment rates, and acceptance rates.
Find U.S. college essay prompts all in one place, updated and vetted by the Cialfo team.
School Costs keep you up-to-date on the true cost of attending a college, including in-state versus out-of-state fees and a breakdown of fiancial aid awarded.
Explore 25000+ colleges in 36 countries with rankings, statistics, and financial data.
Application History lets you keep track of past students and their admission outcomes across multiple years.
Plot students scores on a scattergram across your school - or the Cialfo network at large.

Integrate your Google or Microsoft calendars so students can book meetings directly with you or assign assessments through YouScience, while Cialfos database of college information collects all the research you need in one place.

homePageFeaturesLeverageBlurb.en-US: Reduce friction for students by building workflows and automations for them in Resources. With all the requirements and tasks clearly defined for students, college applications suddenly seem a lot less overwhelming.

solutionsSubfooterQuote.en-US: Setting up Cialfo was a breeze  their engineering team say down with us and really took the time to go over all our requirements.

marqueeContent.en-US: Hearing Cialfo say you guys are already working on this or that, and that you welcome our ideas and want to work with our feedback... that team feeling is great. That's a major reason we chose Cialfo.

aboutPageBusinessAdvisorBlurb.en-US: Sarah graduated from Harvard University with a Masters degree in International Education, where she was a J.D. Admissions Reader at the Harvard Law School. Sarah started her career at a management consulting firm where she worked with Fortune 500 companies and subsequently joined an education organization in San Francisco where she helped open college preparatory schools in California. She now advises a portfolio of education and edtech companies.

ediBlurb.en-US: Edi is a Google Chrome extension that lets you research, browse, and discover essay prompts from any page in Google Chrome.

vpnBlurb.en-US: Cialfo works on WeChat so you don't have to switch apps to use Cialfo. Send messages, schedule meetings, or check on your tasks  right from within WeChat

aboutPageBusinessAdvisorBlurb.en-US: We're heading to Louisville, KY, and we're hosting a user session! Join us to learn how other expert counselors are leveraging Cialfo at their schools.

homePageHeaderTitle.en-US: Help students and employees alike succeed

homePageHeaderBlurb.en-US: Cialfo designs technology that unifies, simplifies, and secures your education ecosystem.

homePageSchoolTestimonialsTitle.en-US: Field Disabled (The best international schools trust Cialfo)

homePageFeaturesSendDocumentTitle.en-US: Improve student success with machine learning and big data

homePageFeaturesSendDocumentBlurb.en-US: Data dashboards provide your educators with 360 degree views of student outcomes at a class, school or district level. Use Reports to discover how many of your students are matriculating into colleges or taking a gap year, where theyre going after K12, and what post-secondary programs are succeeding. Compare outcomes against past years or cohorts, and discover trends in applications and student ambitions.

homePageFeaturesLeverageTitle.en-US: Reduce costs and simplify district operations

homePageFeaturesLeverageBlurb.en-US: Ease your district budgets and maximize resources by centralizing college operations across all your schools. Cialfo Districts brings together counselors, district managers, administrators and superintendents into one unified platform to reduce costs and funnel resources into student outcomes.

solutionsSubfooterQuote.en-US: Setting up Cialfo was a breeze  their engineering team say down with us and really took the time to go over all our requirements.

homePageHeaderTitle.en-US: Top performing principals use Cialfo to manage their schools

homePageHeaderBlurb.en-US: Get unparalleled access into your data. Cialfo empowers data-driven principals and administrators to analyze, visualize, and share reports. Want to know your application history over the last 10 years or trends in college destinations? Now you can.

homePageSchoolTestimonialsTitle.en-US: Field Disabled (The best international schools trust Cialfo)

homePageFeaturesSendDocumentBlurb.en-US: Can your school or district measure key college counseling success metrics? Track college outcomes and report results in an easily exportable spreadsheet. Use Reports to discover application histories, measure student success based on ethnicity or gender, and forecast college application trends.

homePageFeaturesLeverageTitle.en-US: One platform for teachers, counselors, students, and parents

homePageFeaturesLeverageBlurb.en-US: When you subscribe to Cialfo, you only pay for your graduating class. All other students receive access to Cialfo so college prep can begin early. Guardians and parents can track their childs college application process with separate logins, while teachers use Teacher Accounts to submit and manage letters of recommendation.

aboutPageBusinessAdvisorBlurb.en-US: Prior to joining Dhirubhai Ambani International School, Barry was a college counselor at the American International School of Lagos and International School of Beijing. Barry holds an MEd in School Counseling from University of Southern Queensland and currently serves as Deputy Head of Secondary at Oberoi International School.

As the President of Taylor's Education Group, former Executive Vice President at Blackboard, and former Managing Director of the Nobel Education Network, Karl has deep experience in building and scaling education technology companies. His expertise spans across business development, strategy, and operations roles at Nobel Education Network, Pearson, Blackboard, Campus Direct and The Princeton Review.

Bob Patterson is currently the CEO of BE Education. At Chegg, Bob was previously Vice President of Student Success and later a Chegg Foundation Board Member. He brings a deep expertise in college admissions from his experience in admissions offices at Stanford University, UC Berkeley, and UNC Chapel Hill. Bob also served as an elected delegate on the National Association of College Admission Counseling (NACAC).

As Head of University Guidance at YCIS, John brings 15 years of education to Cialfo's advisory board. John was formerly Director of Counseling at International Bilingual School at Hsinchu Science Park, and holds an MEd in Independent School Leadership as well as an MA in Educational Leadership from Teachers College of Columbia University.

As Head of College Counseling at Aditya Birla World Academy, Sonia brings almost 14 years of experience to our board. Sonia holds a Doctorate of Psychology from the Maharastra University,  a Graduate Certificate in College Counselling from UCLA & a Certificate in College Admissions from  Harvard Summer Institute at Harvard University.

Formerly Assistant Director of Admissions at Columbia University, Terry later switched to college counseling posts as Co-Director of College Counseling and Academic Counselor (grades 10-12) at Oakwood School and later Co-Director of College Counseling and Admission Associate for Outreach at Immaculate Heart School. Terry earned her B.A. in Political Science and Masters in Higher Education Administration from Columbia.

With over 30 years of experience in college admissions and financial aid, Katy was a past president of the National Association for College Admission Counseling (NACAC) as well as the Western Association for College Admission Counseling (WACAC). Katy is an instructor at the UC Berkeley and UCLA Extension College Counseling Certificate Programs and currently serves the Director of College Counseling at Bellarmine College Preparatory.

Prior to joining The Epsicopal Academy, Cynthia was previously Director of College Counseling at Whitfield School. She brings 13 years of experience from the other side of the desk as Assistant Director of Undergraduate Admission at Washington University, and earned her A.B in English from Washington University in St. Louis.

Peggy Hock received both her bachelors and Ph.D. degrees in psychology from Columbia University. She was an assistant professor of psychology at Dartmouth College and a research scientist at Stanford University, has been the director of college counseling at three San Francisco Bay area private high schools, and is currently an instructor in the UC Berkeley College Counseling Certificate Program. She is a past-president of the Western Association for College Admissions Counseling.

Originally from New York and Northern Virginia, Karen graduated from Columbia University with a B.S. in Applied Mathematics. Not ready to leave academia, she worked in the Undergraduate Admissions at both Dartmouth College and Columbia University.  While at Columbia, she completed her M.A. in Higher and Postsecondary Education followed by a Certificate Program in International Counseling at Lehigh University. Karen made the transition to the other side of the desk and began university counseling at the Potomac School, outside Washington, DC.  With an avid love of travel and adventure, Karen found she was spending every summer exploring new countries and cultures, which influenced her decision to move to Belgium to join the International School of Brussels counseling team. Karen is currently IB/AP Coordinator at International School Manila.
